  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "A fundamental characteristic of the human visual system is its ability to selectively focus on salient aspects of a scene rather than processing the entire visual field simultaneously.",
    "This selective attention enables enhanced capture of visual details [45].",
    "In recent years, researchers have developed various selective attention mechanisms for neural networks.",
    "These mechanisms enable neural networks to learn \"where\" or \"what\" to focus more on, using explicit dependencies between channels and weighted spatial regions.",
    "In this context, the convolutional block attention module (CBAM) was introduced by Woo et al. [46] as an efficient attention mechanism designed for CNNs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "This selective attention enables enhanced capture of visual details [45].",
